I'd like to say some things to any aspiring writefrens,
You'll never get started if you don't start.
Your first draft will always be rough.
You will never get better if you don't keep writing.
The more you write the more you will find your writing style and voice.
Find a discord or community to read and give feedback, a beta reader is an amazing partner to work hone your stories.
Write what you enjoy and others will enjoy it, but keep a mind to your audience's taste.
Most of all, have fun and be overly critical of yourself.
You may never be the next Tolkien or Hemingway, but you'll have an audience who will enjoy your work.
Now get out there and write dogoneit
